Package edu.sdsc.mmtf.spark.filters

Classes to filter structures.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ContainsAlternativeLocations
    This filter return true if this structure contains an alternative location.
    ContainsDnaChain
    This filter passes entries that contain DNA chains.
    ContainsDProteinChain
    This filter returns entries that contain protein chain(s) made of D-amino acids.
    ContainsDSaccharideChain
    This filter returns entries that contain chain(s) made of linear and branched D-saccharides.
    ContainsGroup
    This filter returns entries that contain specified groups (residues).
    ContainsLProteinChain
    This filter returns entries that contain polymer chain(s) made of L-amino acids.
    ContainsPolymerChainType
    This filter returns entries that contain chains made of the specified monomer types.
    ContainsRnaChain
    This filter passes entries that contain RNA chains.
    ContainsSequenceRegex
    This filter returns true if the polymer sequence motif matches the specified regular expression.
    ExperimentalMethods
    This filter returns true if all the specified experimental methods match a PDB entry.
    NotFilter
    This filter wraps another filter and negates its result.
    OrFilter
    This filter wraps two filter and returns true if one of the filters passes.
    PolymerComposition
    This filter returns chains with the specified monomers.
    Resolution
    This filter return true if the resolution value for this structure is within the specified range.
    Rfree
    This filter return true if the rFree value for this structure is within the specified range.
    Rwork
    This filter return true if the r-work value for this structure is within the specified range.
    SecondaryStructure
    This filter returns entries that contain polymer chain(s) with the specified fraction of secondary structure assignments, obtained by DSSP.
